<br>
Evade as it works now, when successful, reduces your 'hate points' to 120 instantly. A person that just entered into agro range of a mob has 128 points of hate.<br>
<br>
With the old hate list only holding six people, and rolling the lowest off, a high damage rogue had a good chance of promoting himself right back up the hate list in a hurry, requiring multiple evades during a fight. <br>
<br>
Combined with the roughly 30% chance that a rogue would fail to evade, along with timing issues (not moving, not getting hit, etc), and shorter encounter times, Evade was somewhat self balancing.<br>
<br>
With the changes made prior to shipping Velious, the hate list now holds sixty players, so ONE successful evade by a rogue in a large scale encounter was usually enough to keep him from ever being directly attacked. Like I said, a player just walking into awareness range of a mob had more hate than a rogue did right after evading.<br>
<br>
Just to give you some examples of hate generation, any buff/heal cast on a party member in combat generates about 400 hate, a Ykesha proc generates roughly double that, Snares and debuff effects even more, and melee hits can range from 50-500 points per hit. <br>
<br>
This is what is out of whack, the rogue is potentially not responsible for ANY damage or effects he deals out, barring bad timing preventing him from evading. It is not uncommon for a rogue, if he does not Evade, to generate 10, 20, even 50k of hate in an encounter, yet Evade negates ALL of it.<br>
<br>
Our proposed change, which I am firmly in support of, is to change the way Evade modifies your hate points. We're looking at having Evade reduce your total hate by 33%, rather than setting it to a flat 120. <br>
<br>
This COULD mean that an Evade will still leave you at the top of the hate list, depending on how much damage you dealt vs. what the rest of the party/raid is doing. <br>
<br>
This may require you to rely more on taunters in the group, modify your damage output, ease up on procs, etc. But in general, it will only have an impact in multi-group situations at high levels. <br>
<br>
Even then, you can STILL mitigate it, since Evades will be cumulative. 10k of hate becomes 6.6k of hate becomes 4.4k becomes 3k and so on. But there is still 10 seconds per attempt, chance of failure and timing issues to keep it in check.<br>
<br>
This does not spell doom for the rogue class, it simply makes them more responsible for their damage output, but it will not bring back the 'bad old days' pre-Evade. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utzeendao.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzeen Dao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/5/01 4:58:14 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/tzeendao/images/pip.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What we are proposing for Evade.</span><hr size=1> Nifty.  Thanks for the info.<br>
